23const int kMaxAbsQpDeltaValue = 51;
24const int kMinQpValue = 0;
25const int kMaxQpValue = 51;

31#define RETURN_ON_FAIL(x, res) \
32 do { \
33 if (!(x)) { \
34 RTC_LOG_F(LS_ERROR) << "FAILED: " #x; \
35 return res; \
36 } \
37 } while (0)
38
39#define RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(x) RETURN_ON_FAIL(x, kInvalidStream)
40
41H264BitstreamParser::H264BitstreamParser() {}
42H264BitstreamParser::~H264BitstreamParser() {}
43
44H264BitstreamParser::Result H264BitstreamParser::ParseNonParameterSetNalu(
45 const uint8_t* source,
46 size_t source_length,
47 uint8_t nalu_type) {
48 if (!sps_ || !pps_)
49 return kInvalidStream;
50
51 last_slice_qp_delta_ = absl::nullopt;
52 const std::vector<uint8_t> slice_rbsp =
53 H264::ParseRbsp(source, source_length);
54 if (slice_rbsp.size() < H264::kNaluTypeSize)
55 return kInvalidStream;
56
57 rtc::BitBuffer slice_reader(slice_rbsp.data() + H264::kNaluTypeSize,
58 slice_rbsp.size() - H264::kNaluTypeSize);
59 // Check to see if this is an IDR slice, which has an extra field to parse
60 // out.
61 bool is_idr = (source[0] & 0x0F) == H264::NaluType::kIdr;
62 uint8_t nal_ref_idc = (source[0] & 0x60) >> 5;
63 uint32_t golomb_tmp;
64 uint32_t bits_tmp;
65
66 // first_mb_in_slice: ue(v)
67 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
68 // slice_type: ue(v)
69 uint32_t slice_type;
70 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(slice_type));
71 // slice_type's 5..9 range is used to indicate that all slices of a picture
72 // have the same value of slice_type % 5, we don't care about that, so we map
73 // to the corresponding 0..4 range.
74 slice_type %= 5;
75 // pic_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
76 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
77 if (sps_->separate_colour_plane_flag == 1) {
78 // colour_plane_id
79 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadBits(2, bits_tmp));
80 }
81 // frame_num: u(v)
82 // Represented by log2_max_frame_num bits.
83 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadBits(sps_->log2_max_frame_num, bits_tmp));
84 uint32_t field_pic_flag = 0;
85 if (sps_->frame_mbs_only_flag == 0) {
86 // field_pic_flag: u(1)
87 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadBits(1, field_pic_flag));
88 if (field_pic_flag != 0) {
89 // bottom_field_flag: u(1)
90 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadBits(1, bits_tmp));
91 }
92 }
93 if (is_idr) {
94 // idr_pic_id: ue(v)
95 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
96 }
97 // pic_order_cnt_lsb: u(v)
98 // Represented by sps_.log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb bits.
99 if (sps_->pic_order_cnt_type == 0) {
100 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
101 slice_reader.ReadBits(sps_->log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb, bits_tmp));
102 if (pps_->bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag &&
103 field_pic_flag == 0) {
104 // delta_pic_order_cnt_bottom: se(v)
105 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
106 }
107 }
108 if (sps_->pic_order_cnt_type == 1 &&
109 !sps_->delta_pic_order_always_zero_flag) {
110 // delta_pic_order_cnt[0]: se(v)
111 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
112 if (pps_->bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag && !field_pic_flag) {
113 // delta_pic_order_cnt[1]: se(v)
114 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
115 }
116 }
117 if (pps_->redundant_pic_cnt_present_flag) {
118 // redundant_pic_cnt: ue(v)
119 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
120 }
121 if (slice_type == H264::SliceType::kB) {
122 // direct_spatial_mv_pred_flag: u(1)
123 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadBits(1, bits_tmp));
124 }
125 switch (slice_type) {
126 case H264::SliceType::kP:
127 case H264::SliceType::kB:
128 case H264::SliceType::kSp:
129 uint32_t num_ref_idx_active_override_flag;
130 // num_ref_idx_active_override_flag: u(1)
131 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
132 slice_reader.ReadBits(1, num_ref_idx_active_override_flag));
133 if (num_ref_idx_active_override_flag != 0) {
134 // num_ref_idx_l0_active_minus1: ue(v)
135 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
136 if (slice_type == H264::SliceType::kB) {
137 // num_ref_idx_l1_active_minus1: ue(v)
138 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
139 }
140 }
141 break;
142 default:
143 break;
144 }
145 // assume nal_unit_type != 20 && nal_unit_type != 21:
146 if (nalu_type == 20 || nalu_type == 21) {
147 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unsupported nal unit type.";
148 return kUnsupportedStream;
149 }
150 // if (nal_unit_type == 20 || nal_unit_type == 21)
151 // ref_pic_list_mvc_modification()
152 // else
153 {
154 // ref_pic_list_modification():
155 // |slice_type| checks here don't use named constants as they aren't named
156 // in the spec for this segment. Keeping them consistent makes it easier to
157 // verify that they are both the same.
158 if (slice_type % 5 != 2 && slice_type % 5 != 4) {
159 // ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l0: u(1)
160 uint32_t ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l0;
161 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
162 slice_reader.ReadBits(1, ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l0));
163 if (ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l0) {
164 uint32_t modification_of_pic_nums_idc;
165 do {
166 // modification_of_pic_nums_idc: ue(v)
167 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
168 slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(modification_of_pic_nums_idc));
169 if (modification_of_pic_nums_idc == 0 ||
170 modification_of_pic_nums_idc == 1) {
171 // abs_diff_pic_num_minus1: ue(v)
172 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
173 } else if (modification_of_pic_nums_idc == 2) {
174 // long_term_pic_num: ue(v)
175 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
176 }
177 } while (modification_of_pic_nums_idc != 3);
178 }
179 }
180 if (slice_type % 5 == 1) {
181 // ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l1: u(1)
182 uint32_t ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l1;
183 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
184 slice_reader.ReadBits(1, ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l1));
185 if (ref_pic_list_modification_flag_l1) {
186 uint32_t modification_of_pic_nums_idc;
187 do {
188 // modification_of_pic_nums_idc: ue(v)
189 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
190 slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(modification_of_pic_nums_idc));
191 if (modification_of_pic_nums_idc == 0 ||
192 modification_of_pic_nums_idc == 1) {
193 // abs_diff_pic_num_minus1: ue(v)
194 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
195 } else if (modification_of_pic_nums_idc == 2) {
196 // long_term_pic_num: ue(v)
197 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
198 }
199 } while (modification_of_pic_nums_idc != 3);
200 }
201 }
202 }
203 // TODO(pbos): Do we need support for pred_weight_table()?
204 if ((pps_->weighted_pred_flag && (slice_type == H264::SliceType::kP ||
205 slice_type == H264::SliceType::kSp)) ||
206 (pps_->weighted_bipred_idc == 1 && slice_type == H264::SliceType::kB)) {
207 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Streams with pred_weight_table unsupported.";
208 return kUnsupportedStream;
209 }
210 // if ((weighted_pred_flag && (slice_type == P || slice_type == SP)) ||
211 // (weighted_bipred_idc == 1 && slice_type == B)) {
212 // pred_weight_table()
213 // }
214 if (nal_ref_idc != 0) {
215 // dec_ref_pic_marking():
216 if (is_idr) {
217 // no_output_of_prior_pics_flag: u(1)
218 // long_term_reference_flag: u(1)
219 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadBits(2, bits_tmp));
220 } else {
221 // adaptive_ref_pic_marking_mode_flag: u(1)
222 uint32_t adaptive_ref_pic_marking_mode_flag;
223 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
224 slice_reader.ReadBits(1, adaptive_ref_pic_marking_mode_flag));
225 if (adaptive_ref_pic_marking_mode_flag) {
226 uint32_t memory_management_control_operation;
227 do {
228 // memory_management_control_operation: ue(v)
229 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(
230 memory_management_control_operation));
231 if (memory_management_control_operation == 1 ||
232 memory_management_control_operation == 3) {
233 // difference_of_pic_nums_minus1: ue(v)
234 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
235 }
236 if (memory_management_control_operation == 2) {
237 // long_term_pic_num: ue(v)
238 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
239 }
240 if (memory_management_control_operation == 3 ||
241 memory_management_control_operation == 6) {
242 // long_term_frame_idx: ue(v)
243 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
244 }
245 if (memory_management_control_operation == 4) {
246 // max_long_term_frame_idx_plus1: ue(v)
247 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
248 }
249 } while (memory_management_control_operation != 0);
250 }
251 }
252 }
253 if (pps_->entropy_coding_mode_flag && slice_type != H264::SliceType::kI &&
254 slice_type != H264::SliceType::kSi) {
255 // cabac_init_idc: ue(v)
256 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp));
257 }
258
259 int32_t last_slice_qp_delta;
260 RETURN_INV_ON_FAIL(
261 slice_reader.ReadSignedExponentialGolomb(last_slice_qp_delta));
262 if (abs(last_slice_qp_delta) > kMaxAbsQpDeltaValue) {
263 // Something has gone wrong, and the parsed value is invalid.
264 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Parsed QP value out of range.";
265 return kInvalidStream;
266 }
267
268 last_slice_qp_delta_ = last_slice_qp_delta;
269 return kOk;
270}
271
272void H264BitstreamParser::ParseSlice(const uint8_t* slice, size_t length) {
273 H264::NaluType nalu_type = H264::ParseNaluType(slice[0]);
274 switch (nalu_type) {
275 case H264::NaluType::kSps: {
276 sps_ = SpsParser::ParseSps(slice + H264::kNaluTypeSize,
277 length - H264::kNaluTypeSize);
278 if (!sps_)
279 RTC_DLOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unable to parse SPS from H264 bitstream.";
280 break;
281 }
282 case H264::NaluType::kPps: {
283 pps_ = PpsParser::ParsePps(slice + H264::kNaluTypeSize,
284 length - H264::kNaluTypeSize);
285 if (!pps_)
286 RTC_DLOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unable to parse PPS from H264 bitstream.";
287 break;
288 }
289 case H264::NaluType::kAud:
290 case H264::NaluType::kSei:
291 break; // Ignore these nalus, as we don't care about their contents.
292 default:
293 Result res = ParseNonParameterSetNalu(slice, length, nalu_type);
294 if (res != kOk)
295 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "Failed to parse bitstream. Error: " << res;
296 break;
297 }
298}
299
300void H264BitstreamParser::ParseBitstream(
301 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> bitstream) {
302 std::vector<H264::NaluIndex> nalu_indices =
303 H264::FindNaluIndices(bitstream.data(), bitstream.size());
304 for (const H264::NaluIndex& index : nalu_indices)
305 ParseSlice(bitstream.data() + index.payload_start_offset,
306 index.payload_size);
307}
308
309absl::optional<int> H264BitstreamParser::GetLastSliceQp() const {
310 if (!last_slice_qp_delta_ || !pps_)
311 return absl::nullopt;
312 const int qp = 26 + pps_->pic_init_qp_minus26 + *last_slice_qp_delta_;
313 if (qp < kMinQpValue || qp > kMaxQpValue) {
314 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Parsed invalid QP from bitstream.";
315 return absl::nullopt;
316 }
317 return qp;
318}
